   "source": [
    "# Problem Sheet 2 example answers"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# We always start with appropriate imports; note the use of the IPython magic\n",
    "# command to set up Matplotlib within the notebook\n",
    "%matplotlib inline\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import matplotlib.colors as colors"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Question 1\n",
    "\n",
    "### Part (a)\n",
    "\n",
    "I decided to make a function for the potential; in order to be able to operate on the arrays,  I'm working with separate x and y terms.  Note that I have used the 'xy' argument with `np.meshgrid` so that it is compatible with `plt.contourf`"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def es_potential(q,x1,y1,x2,y2):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Calculate the electrostatic potential at r2 for a charge q at r1.\n",
    "    Atomic units are used.  Two dimensions only.\n",
    "    Inputs:\n",
    "    q      Charge\n",
    "    x1, y1 Location of charge\n",
    "    x2, y2 Location of potential to be calculated\n",
    "    Outputs:\n",
    "    Potential\"\"\"\n",
    "    dx = x1 - x2\n",
    "    dy = y1 - y2\n",
    "    dr2 = dx*dx + dy*dy\n",
    "    dr = np.sqrt(dr2)\n",
    "    return q/dr"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "delta = 0.1\n",
    "npts = int(10/delta + 1)\n",
    "q1x = np.linspace(-5,5,npts)\n",
    "q1y = np.linspace(-5,5,npts)\n",
    "q1x_2d, q1y_2d = np.meshgrid(q1x,q1y,indexing='xy')\n",
    "potential = np.zeros((npts,npts))\n",
    "x_q1 = -1.05\n",
    "y_q1 = 0.0\n",
    "x_q2 = 1.05\n",
    "y_q2 = 0.0\n",
    "potential = es_potential(1,x_q1,y_q1,q1x_2d,q1y_2d)\n",
    "potential += es_potential(-1,x_q2,y_q2,q1x_2d,q1y_2d)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Part (b)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "(-5.0, 5.0, -5.0, 5.0)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 4,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plt.imshow(potential,norm=colors.SymLogNorm(0.1),extent=(-5,5,-5,5),origin='lower')\n",
    "contours = [-0.1,-0.05,-0.02,0.02,0.05,0.1]\n",
    "plt.contour(q1x_2d,q1y_2d,potential,contours)\n",
    "plt.axis('scaled')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Part (c)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "(-4.999999999999999, 4.9999999999999645, -5.0, 4.9999999999999645)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 5,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# x\n",
    "dphi_p = np.roll(potential,-1,axis=1)\n",
    "dphi_p[-1] = 0 # Boundary\n",
    "dphi_m = np.roll(potential,1,axis=1)\n",
    "dphi_m[0] = 0 # Boundary\n",
    "dE_dx = (dphi_p - dphi_m)/(2*delta)\n",
    "# y\n",
    "dphi_p = np.roll(potential,-1,axis=0)\n",
    "dphi_p[:,-1] = 0 # Boundary\n",
    "dphi_m = np.roll(potential,1,axis=0)\n",
    "dphi_m[:,0] = 0 # Boundary\n",
    "dE_dy = (dphi_p - dphi_m)/(2*delta)\n",
    "plt.streamplot(q1x,q1y,dE_dx,dE_dy)\n",
    "plt.axis('scaled')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Here is a calculation of the analytic field; we adapt the existing potential function, and return components separately"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def es_field(q,x1,y1,x2,y2):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Calculate the electrostatic field at r2 for a charge q at r1.\n",
    "    Atomic units are used.  Two dimensions only.\n",
    "    Inputs:\n",
    "    q      Charge\n",
    "    x1, y1 Location of charge\n",
    "    x2, y2 Location of field to be calculated\n",
    "    Outputs:\n",
    "    Potential\"\"\"\n",
    "    dx = x1 - x2\n",
    "    dy = y1 - y2\n",
    "    dr2 = dx*dx + dy*dy\n",
    "    dr = np.sqrt(dr2)\n",
    "    return q*dx/(dr*dr2), q*dy/(dr*dr2)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "(-4.999999999999999, 4.9999999999999645, -5.0, 4.9999999999999645)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 7,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "dEdx_ana = np.zeros((npts,npts))\n",
    "dEdy_ana = np.zeros((npts,npts))\n",
    "dEdx_ana, dEdy_ana = es_field(1,x_q1,y_q1,q1x_2d,q1y_2d)\n",
    "E2x, E2y = es_field(-1,x_q2,y_q2,q1x_2d,q1y_2d)\n",
    "dEdx_ana += E2x\n",
    "dEdy_ana += E2y\n",
    "plt.streamplot(q1x,q1y,dEdx_ana,dEdy_ana)\n",
    "plt.axis('scaled')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Another way to calculate the electric field (or the potential) is shown below"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "(-4.999999999999999, 4.9999999999999645, -5.0, 4.9999999999999645)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 8,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "denom = (np.sqrt((q1x_2d - x_q2)**2 + (q1y_2d - y_q2)**2))**3\n",
    "Epx = (q1x_2d - x_q2)/denom\n",
    "Epy = (q1y_2d - y_q2)/denom\n",
    "denom = (np.sqrt((q1x_2d - x_q1)**2 + (q1y_2d - y_q1)**2))**3\n",
    "Epx -= (q1x_2d - x_q1)/denom\n",
    "Epy -= (q1y_2d - y_q1)/denom\n",
    "plt.streamplot(q1x,q1y,Epx,Epy)\n",
    "plt.axis('scaled')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Question 2\n",
    "\n",
    "### Part (a)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "[<matplotlib.lines.Line2D at 0x119a67e10>]"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 9,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "r = np.arange(0,20,0.2)\n",
    "dens = r*np.exp(-2*r)\n",
    "plt.plot(r,dens)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "A maximum range of 10 bohr looks sensible; we can check this by evaluating the magnitude of the function:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Magnitude of density at 10 bohr is  2.061153622438558e-08\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "print(\"Magnitude of density at 10 bohr is \",10*np.exp(-2*10))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Part (b)\n",
    "\n",
    "We will now redefine `r` and integrate"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "With  11  points, the integral is  0.23767948416122733\n",
      "With  101  points, the integral is  0.24999822442549968\n",
      "With  1001  points, the integral is  0.24999988595150924\n",
      "With  10001  points, the integral is  0.24999988612121476\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from scipy import integrate\n",
    "for npts in (11,101,1001,10001):\n",
    "    r = np.linspace(0,10,npts)\n",
    "    dens = r*np.exp(-2*r)\n",
    "    tot = integrate.trapz(r*dens,r)\n",
    "    print(\"With \",npts,\" points, the integral is \",tot)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We can see that 101 points gives a good convergence.  The value of A should be $2/\\pi$.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Part (c)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Total charge is:  0.9999986726464645\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "A = 2.0/np.pi\n",
    "N = 1001\n",
    "xymin = -10\n",
    "xymax = +10\n",
    "delta = (xymax-xymin)/(N-1)\n",
    "x2 = np.linspace(xymin,xymax,N)\n",
    "y2 = np.linspace(xymin,xymax,N)\n",
    "a2,b2 = np.meshgrid(x2,y2,indexing='xy')\n",
    "r = np.sqrt(a2*a2 + b2*b2)\n",
    "dens_grid = A*r*np.exp(-2*r)\n",
    "# Check overall integral\n",
    "print(\"Total charge is: \",np.sum(dens_grid)*delta*delta)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We find that 101 points is not enough in 2D, giving an error in the charge of 0.02 electrons, so have moved to 1001.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Part (d)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Total energy is  -1.0000023156696676\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "prod = -A*(np.exp(-2*r))\n",
    "print(\"Total energy is \",np.sum(prod)*delta*delta)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Part (e)\n",
    "\n",
    "We will now loop over different numbers of points and test the energy"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "101  points with spacing  0.2\n",
      "Total charge is:  0.9988463600494522\n",
      "Total energy is  -1.0023228235395665\n",
      "201  points with spacing  0.1\n",
      "Total charge is:  0.999854549251662\n",
      "Total energy is  -1.0002910850445224\n",
      "501  points with spacing  0.04\n",
      "Total charge is:  0.9999905216260512\n",
      "Total energy is  -1.0000186289857698\n",
      "1001  points with spacing  0.02\n",
      "Total charge is:  0.9999986726464645\n",
      "Total energy is  -1.0000023156696676\n",
      "10001  points with spacing  0.002\n",
      "Total charge is:  0.9999998340065925\n",
      "Total energy is  -0.9999999870272948\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "for N in (101,201,501,1001,10001):\n",
    "    delta = (xymax-xymin)/(N-1)\n",
    "    print(N,\" points with spacing \",delta)\n",
    "    x2 = np.linspace(xymin,xymax,N)\n",
    "    y2 = np.linspace(xymin,xymax,N)\n",
    "    a2,b2 = np.meshgrid(x2,y2,indexing='xy')\n",
    "    r = np.sqrt(a2*a2 + b2*b2)\n",
    "    dens_grid = A*r*np.exp(-2*r)\n",
    "    print(\"Total charge is: \",np.sum(dens_grid)*delta*delta)\n",
    "    prod = -A*(np.exp(-2*r))\n",
    "    print(\"Total energy is \",np.sum(prod)*delta*delta)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We see that convergence to better than one percent is achieved with 101 points, while almost complete convergence is reached at 10,001 points but the calculation takes several seconds.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Question 3"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Part a (Euler)\n",
    "\n",
    "We need to re-arrange to find $d\\theta/dx = -(Q/\\kappa)/A(x)$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 15,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def bar_area(x,theta):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Calculate RHS of heat equation\"\"\"\n",
    "    Qk = 0.05\n",
    "    return -Qk*1e4/((2-x)*(2-x))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 16,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "[<matplotlib.lines.Line2D at 0x151df5cda0>]"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 16,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "t0 = 500\n",
    "dtdx = 0\n",
    "xgrid = np.linspace(0.01,1,100)\n",
    "theta = np.zeros(101)\n",
    "theta[0] = t0\n",
    "for i, x in enumerate(xgrid):\n",
    "    theta[i+1] = theta[i] + 0.01*bar_area(x,theta[i])\n",
    "xplt = np.linspace(0,1,101)\n",
    "plt.plot(xplt,theta)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Part (b)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 17,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from scipy import integrate"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 18,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "solution = integrate.solve_ivp(bar_area,(0,1),np.array([500]))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 19,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "[<matplotlib.lines.Line2D at 0x1199e0780>]"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 19,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plt.plot(solution.t,solution.y[0])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Part (c)\n",
    "\n",
    "Recall that `odeint` takes the opposite order of arguments to `solve_ivp`.  Also note that we need to solve for $\\theta = 300$K, so we will subtract 300K from the value of the temperature at the end of the bar to be able to use a root-finding algorithm."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 20,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def bar_area_Q(theta,x,Qk):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Calculate RHS of heat equation\"\"\"\n",
    "    return -Qk*1e4/((2-x)*(2-x))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 21,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Starting values:  [200.] [-48.74377671]\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "theta0 = 500\n",
    "Qk0 = 0.0\n",
    "RHS0 = integrate.odeint(bar_area_Q,theta0,xgrid,args=(Qk0,))[-1]-300\n",
    "Qk1 = 0.05\n",
    "RHS1 = integrate.odeint(bar_area_Q,theta0,xgrid,args=(Qk1,))[-1]-300\n",
    "print(\"Starting values: \",RHS0,RHS1)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 22,
   "metadata": {
    "scrolled": false
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "dx, df:  0.05 [-248.74377671]\n",
      "dx, df:  [-0.00979799] [48.74376488]\n",
      "After  2  iterations, Q/k is  [0.04020201]\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "tol = 1e-4\n",
    "n = 0\n",
    "while abs(RHS0) > tol:\n",
    "    n += 1\n",
    "    # Calculate next point\n",
    "    dx = Qk1 - Qk0\n",
    "    df = RHS1 - RHS0\n",
    "    print(\"dx, df: \",dx,df)\n",
    "    xnext = Qk1 - RHS1 * dx / df\n",
    "    # Update storage\n",
    "    Qk0 = Qk1\n",
    "    Qk1 = xnext\n",
    "    RHS0 = RHS1\n",
    "    RHS1 = integrate.odeint(bar_area_Q,theta0,xgrid,args=(Qk1,))[-1]-300\n",
    "print(\"After \",n,\" iterations, Q/k is \",Qk1)"
   ]
  },
